Maybe I can help them.

763
01:01:14,309 --> 01:01:16,183
They got checkpoints
all over the place.

764
01:01:16,267 --> 01:01:17,933
You think you can make it?

765
01:01:18,017 --> 01:01:20,641
I have a friend
who knows where they are.

766
01:01:20,725 --> 01:01:23,058
I think he can help me.

767
01:01:25,225 --> 01:01:27,891
Will I see you again?

768
01:01:54,058 --> 01:01:56,309
Fireman: Keep searching
for that Omnis!

769
01:01:59,267 --> 01:02:01,933
- Montag: Get 'em out of here!
- Fireman: Yes, sir.

770
01:02:15,142 --> 01:02:17,267
All clear.
Let's check upstairs.

771
01:02:19,100 --> 01:02:21,600
- ( clatter )
- Man: Shh!

772
01:02:31,559 --> 01:02:34,517
( opens door,
pulls back curtain )

773
01:02:58,434 --> 01:03:00,517
( rain pattering )

774
01:03:20,350 --> 01:03:24,392
Beatty: And how would you explain
your behavior today?

775
01:03:24,475 --> 01:03:26,309
I fucked up.

776
01:03:28,100 --> 01:03:31,434
- I couldn't tell you why.
- Was it the kid?

777
01:03:31,517 --> 01:03:35,017
Eels use kids as decoys
all the time.

778
01:03:35,100 --> 01:03:39,142
No excuse. I know my actions
put you and the men in danger.

779
01:03:39,225 --> 01:03:41,350
What if they had
had the Omnis?

780
01:03:47,559 --> 01:03:50,725
Captain Beatty...

781
01:03:50,808 --> 01:03:53,517
sir, it's been a true honor.

782
01:03:53,600 --> 01:03:55,392
But...

783
01:03:55,475 --> 01:03:58,766
I respectfully ask
that you accept my resignation.

784
01:04:03,725 --> 01:04:05,267
Get that off my desk.

785
01:04:05,350 --> 01:04:06,350
I'm sorry, John.

786
01:04:06,434 --> 01:04:07,559
Do it. Now.

787
01:04:15,725 --> 01:04:17,891
Are you serious?

788
01:04:17,975 --> 01:04:22,309
I just submitted your name
to replace me as captain.

789
01:04:22,392 --> 01:04:24,142
- It's not about that.
- Oh.

790
01:04:24,225 --> 01:04:26,392
So you're willing
to throw away

791
01:04:26,475 --> 01:04:29,183
the sixteen years
that I've invested in you.

792
01:04:29,267 --> 01:04:32,183
I have sixteen years

793
01:04:32,267 --> 01:04:35,475
of the Ministry's shit
in my head.

794
01:04:35,559 --> 01:04:37,350
And I want to know
why we burn.

795
01:04:37,434 --> 01:04:39,891
- I want to decide.
- Ah.

796
01:04:39,975 --> 01:04:42,517
- So you want to prove you exist.
- Yeah, I do.

797
01:04:42,600 --> 01:04:45,683
I got things inside my head
that don't make sense.

798
01:04:45,766 --> 01:04:47,225
Dreams about my dad.

799
01:04:47,309 --> 01:04:50,017
Look, as your
commanding officer,

800
01:04:50,100 --> 01:04:52,517
it is my duty to report you

801
01:04:52,600 --> 01:04:54,850
for letting two Eels
go free today.

802
01:04:54,933 --> 01:04:57,933
And if I do that, you will
be tried for treason.

803
01:04:58,017 --> 01:05:01,350
And there will be nothing
I can do to protect you.

804
01:05:01,434 --> 01:05:05,142
You betray me...

805
01:05:05,225 --> 01:05:07,017
and I will burn you.

806
01:05:07,100 --> 01:05:10,600
And then I will
burn your ashes.

807
01:05:12,309 --> 01:05:16,350
Dreams are a terror, son.
I know.

808
01:05:16,434 --> 01:05:20,475
But it's just your mind
flingin' itself to pieces.

809
01:05:21,641 --> 01:05:24,891
Just stand back
from the centrifuge, OK?

810
01:05:24,975 --> 01:05:27,225
You have a virus.

811
01:05:27,309 --> 01:05:28,350
Go home...

812
01:05:28,434 --> 01:05:29,808
and rest.

813
01:05:31,142 --> 01:05:32,683
Take a hot bath.

814
01:05:35,517 --> 01:05:37,808
And then you report
to work tomorrow.

815
01:05:37,891 --> 01:05:39,808
But don't make me
come get you.

816
01:05:54,309 --> 01:05:56,142
( clears throat )

817
01:06:00,350 --> 01:06:01,891
Reactivate.

818
01:06:01,975 --> 01:06:03,434
Yuxie:
Hello, John.

819
01:06:03,517 --> 01:06:06,850
Yuxie, get me Fireman Douglas.

820
01:06:11,517 --> 01:06:14,309
Raven: Do your part.
See something, say something.

821
01:06:14,392 --> 01:06:17,142
Tell Yuxie. Together,
we will keep Cleveland...

822
01:06:27,683 --> 01:06:28,975
( tires squeal )

823
01:06:30,808 --> 01:06:33,142
Montag. Get in.

824
01:06:42,891 --> 01:06:44,641
- How'd you find me?
- My friend Gustav...

825
01:06:44,725 --> 01:06:46,392
I'm no friend of his.

826
01:06:46,475 --> 01:06:48,225
Don't look at me.

827
01:06:48,309 --> 01:06:50,933
- Don't fuckin' look at me!
- What's wrong with you?!

828
01:06:51,017 --> 01:06:52,368
You deleted my brother's life,
man!

829
01:06:52,392 --> 01:06:55,850
And you gave him 25 years!
You're scum!

830
01:06:55,933 --> 01:06:57,225
Clarisse:
That's enough.

831
01:07:04,100 --> 01:07:06,142
Gustavo: You better be
right about him.

832
01:07:06,225 --> 01:07:07,808
Where we goin'?

833
01:07:07,891 --> 01:07:09,535
To those people at the compound
I told you about.

834
01:07:09,559 --> 01:07:11,641
- They want to see you.
- For what?

835
01:07:11,725 --> 01:07:15,392
- Something about the Omnis.
- Gustavo: Do it, or I will.

836
01:07:20,309 --> 01:07:21,559
You have to put this on.

837
01:07:46,475 --> 01:07:48,350
Who else was with 'em?

838
01:07:48,434 --> 01:07:51,142
Douglas: I don't know, sir.
Axix-Cam picked up Clarisse.

839
01:07:51,225 --> 01:07:53,933
I knew Montag was a rat.
I told you he wasn't pure.

840
01:07:54,017 --> 01:07:55,641
I didn't ask your opinion!

841
01:07:55,725 --> 01:07:57,641
And the next time
I tell you to follow someone,

842
01:07:57,725 --> 01:07:59,933
you crawl into their asshole!

843
01:08:00,017 --> 01:08:01,559
You hear me?!

844
01:08:02,766 --> 01:08:05,017
Report back to the station.

845
01:08:05,100 --> 01:08:06,434
Yes, sir.

846
01:08:09,392 --> 01:08:11,933
Yuxie:
This is a problem, John.

847
01:08:33,808 --> 01:08:37,017
Clarisse told us
you stole this.

848
01:08:37,100 --> 01:08:39,100
But when I see you
sitting there,

849
01:08:39,183 --> 01:08:41,142
all I can see is fire.

850
01:08:41,225 --> 01:08:45,683
You must be burning all these books,
and us, in your mind.

851
01:08:45,766 --> 01:08:47,891
Because you are what you are,

852
01:08:47,975 --> 01:08:50,142
and perhaps,
that's all you'll ever be...

853
01:08:50,225 --> 01:08:51,434
fire.

854
01:08:51,517 --> 01:08:53,808
This man is just like
his Commandant Beatty.

855
01:08:53,891 --> 01:08:55,600
He's not to be trusted.

856
01:08:55,683 --> 01:08:58,475
Why did you burn books
your whole life?

857
01:08:58,559 --> 01:09:00,600
Because that's all I know.

858
01:09:00,683 --> 01:09:03,142
Deze man is
een stuk stront.

859
01:09:03,225 --> 01:09:05,850
But I want to do
something else.

860
01:09:05,933 --> 01:09:07,850
Why?

861
01:09:15,267 --> 01:09:16,850
When I look at that book,

862
01:09:16,933 --> 01:09:19,183
it made me remember
when I was a kid.

863
01:09:20,975 --> 01:09:24,683
Just sittin' by the ocean...

864
01:09:24,766 --> 01:09:29,434
and I was trying to fill
this sieve with sand.

865
01:09:29,517 --> 01:09:33,725
But the faster I poured,
the faster the sand fell through it.

866
01:09:36,142 --> 01:09:37,891
Lookin' at the words
in that book,

867
01:09:37,975 --> 01:09:41,559
I felt like they... they were
passing right through me.

868
01:09:44,434 --> 01:09:48,434
Like my whole life just...

869
01:09:48,517 --> 01:09:50,808
passed right through me.

870
01:09:50,891 --> 01:09:53,766
And that I missed it.

871
01:09:56,142 --> 01:09:59,058
I'm not gonna let
that happen again.

872
01:10:03,434 --> 01:10:05,766
Books are here
to remind us

873
01:10:05,850 --> 01:10:07,975
what fools we can be.

874
01:10:08,058 --> 01:10:11,350
But if we can remember,
if the Omnis can spread,

875
01:10:11,434 --> 01:10:14,641
then maybe we will win.

876
01:10:14,725 --> 01:10:16,725
The disconnected human mind

877
01:10:16,808 --> 01:10:21,017
is the last bastion
against the technological world.

878
01:10:21,100 --> 01:10:25,600
It's the most secure place
to preserve these books.

879
01:10:25,683 --> 01:10:27,725
We're totally off the grid.

880
01:10:27,808 --> 01:10:31,517
No computers, no way for
you to Firemen to track us

881
01:10:31,600 --> 01:10:34,017
or enter our dreams.

882
01:10:34,100 --> 01:10:37,058
Everything safely here.

883
01:10:37,142 --> 01:10:40,017
- You memorized all these books?
- We each memorize one,

884
01:10:40,100 --> 01:10:42,100
and then we become the book.

885
01:10:42,183 --> 01:10:46,267
I am Toni Morrison.
"Song of Solomon."

886
01:10:46,350 --> 01:10:48,517
He's "The Letters of Van Gogh."

887
01:10:48,600 --> 01:10:52,600
She's Chairman Mao,
"The Little Red Book."

888
01:10:52,683 --> 01:10:56,142
She's Rumi, Darwin,
"Anna Karenina."

889
01:10:56,225 --> 01:10:58,933
And she's half of
"A Yellow Sun."

890
01:10:59,017 --> 01:11:01,350
She's still memorizing it.

891
01:11:01,434 --> 01:11:04,683
In fact, you've met
one of us already.

892
01:11:07,142 --> 01:11:09,392
You took this book
from her library.

893
01:11:09,475 --> 01:11:13,142
She was John Steinbeck's
"The Grapes of Wrath"...

894
01:11:13,225 --> 01:11:16,850
now lost to humanity
forever.

895
01:11:16,933 --> 01:11:20,225
But maybe from her death
we will gain something.

896
01:11:20,309 --> 01:11:22,808
We haven't seen Clarisse
since she was a teen

897
01:11:22,891 --> 01:11:26,017
when she was here
with her parents.

898
01:11:26,100 --> 01:11:30,600
I believe you were memorizing
"White Teeth."

899
01:11:32,142 --> 01:11:34,683
And she tells us
you want to help.

900
01:11:34,766 --> 01:11:38,434
We have an important task
for you related to the Omnis.

901
01:11:38,517 --> 01:11:41,683
But we have to be sure
about you.

902
01:11:42,725 --> 01:11:45,058
Do you know this man?

903
01:11:45,142 --> 01:11:47,683
Fireman Hester.
Fourth District.

904
01:11:47,766 --> 01:11:51,100
That's right.
He's in the back room, waiting for you.

905
01:11:51,183 --> 01:11:53,975
And you're gonna
have to kill him.

906
01:11:54,058 --> 01:11:56,392
Clarisse:
You never told me that.

907
01:12:21,309 --> 01:12:23,058
He's through that door.

908
01:12:24,559 --> 01:12:28,142
A revolution
is not a dinner party.

909
01:12:28,225 --> 01:12:29,850
Good luck.

910
01:12:34,058 --> 01:12:36,517
( door opens, closes )

911
01:12:37,725 --> 01:12:39,392
( switchblade clicks )

912
01:12:42,725 --> 01:12:43,891
( clicks )

913
01:12:45,725 --> 01:12:47,933
( whispers )
They need you, they need you.

914
01:13:23,766 --> 01:13:25,350
Stop!
Put it down!

915
01:13:25,434 --> 01:13:26,975
Hey, man,
what the fuck is this?

916
01:13:27,058 --> 01:13:30,392
You did it.
It's over.

917
01:13:30,475 --> 01:13:32,808
I'm James Baldwin.

918
01:13:32,891 --> 01:13:35,475
"The Fire Next Time."
Welcome.

919
01:13:37,600 --> 01:13:40,267
( leaves rustling )

920
01:14:23,517 --> 01:14:25,309
This way, please.

921
01:14:27,350 --> 01:14:29,267
There's a young man,
Clifford,

922
01:14:29,350 --> 01:14:30,350
in this barn,

923
01:14:30,434 --> 01:14:31,434
in transit to

924
01:14:31,517 --> 01:14:33,267
a group of scientists
in Canada,

925
01:14:33,350 --> 01:14:35,058
and we need you to escort him

926
01:14:35,142 --> 01:14:36,434
over the border.

927
01:14:36,517 --> 01:14:39,058
His mother was a geneticist
behind the Omnis.

928
01:14:39,142 --> 01:14:41,891
Before she died,
she injected the DNA

929
01:14:41,975 --> 01:14:44,725
into Clifford's pet bird.

930
01:14:44,808 --> 01:14:47,267
- The Omnis is in a bird?
- Yes.

931
01:14:47,350 --> 01:14:50,350
We need you to get
them both to safety.

932
01:14:54,517 --> 01:14:58,100
Woman: Clifford?
There's a man here to see you.

933
01:14:58,183 --> 01:15:00,933
Clifford:
Eight. Tagore, Gitanjali,

934
01:15:01,017 --> 01:15:02,309
and poems by Tagore.

935
01:15:02,392 --> 01:15:03,975
It's number eight.

936
01:15:04,058 --> 01:15:06,267
Clarisse:
Has he read all these books?

937
01:15:06,350 --> 01:15:08,641
He's memorized
over 13,000 books.

938
01:15:08,725 --> 01:15:10,165
Clifford:
Pick up a book and test me.

939
01:15:10,225 --> 01:15:12,559
I won't look.
But you'll never win.

940
01:15:21,058 --> 01:15:24,100
Read the title.

941
01:15:25,975 --> 01:15:28,475
- "Remembrance of Things..."
- Remembrance of Things Past."

942
01:15:28,559 --> 01:15:30,933
Marcel Proust, 1927.

943
01:15:31,017 --> 01:15:34,475
3,031 pages, seven volumes,

944
01:15:34,559 --> 01:15:38,225
1,267,069 words.

945
01:15:38,309 --> 01:15:39,683
Open it.

946
01:15:41,183 --> 01:15:42,725
Open it.

947
01:15:48,017 --> 01:15:49,725
Page number... I'll turn around.

948
01:15:49,808 --> 01:15:51,475
No cheating. Page number?

949
01:15:51,559 --> 01:15:55,183
- Page 935.
- 935.

950
01:15:55,267 --> 01:15:57,100
Line 12. Go to line 12.

951
01:15:57,183 --> 01:15:59,683
"So, as long as you distract
your mind from its dreams,

952
01:15:59,766 --> 01:16:02,142
it will not know them
for what they are.

953
01:16:02,225 --> 01:16:05,517
You will always be taken in
by the appearance of things,

954
01:16:05,600 --> 01:16:08,766
because you will not have
grasped their true nature.

955
01:16:08,850 --> 01:16:10,350
If dreaming is dangerous,

956
01:16:10,434 --> 01:16:13,100
then the cure for it
is not to dream less,

957
01:16:13,183 --> 01:16:16,975
but to dream more,
to dream all the time."

958
01:16:18,350 --> 01:16:20,225
Again, test...
test me again.

959
01:16:20,309 --> 01:16:21,600
You'll lose.

960
01:16:30,475 --> 01:16:32,017
Oh, can I show him Lennie?

961
01:16:32,100 --> 01:16:34,350
- Can I?
- Yes.

962
01:16:45,350 --> 01:16:48,017
( chuckling ) Hey.
This is Lennie.

963
01:16:48,100 --> 01:16:52,100
My sturnidae,
from the Latin sturnus.

964
01:16:52,183 --> 01:16:55,309
Medium-sized passerine.
Very gregarious.

965
01:16:55,392 --> 01:16:58,058
Very beautiful.

966
01:16:58,142 --> 01:17:00,267
This is my Lennie.

967
01:17:00,350 --> 01:17:01,434
( bird tweets )

968
01:17:05,975 --> 01:17:07,392
What's up, Lennie?

969
01:17:07,475 --> 01:17:09,517
( chirping )

970
01:17:09,600 --> 01:17:11,475
Montag:
So, what's the next step?

971
01:17:11,559 --> 01:17:13,434
We need a transponder.

972
01:17:13,517 --> 01:17:15,225
The scientists in Canada

973
01:17:15,309 --> 01:17:17,058
are transmitting a homing signal

974
01:17:17,142 --> 01:17:18,891
that will call to a transponder.

975
01:17:18,975 --> 01:17:21,267
Can you get one
and come back tonight?

976
01:17:21,350 --> 01:17:22,850
Yes.

977
01:17:22,933 --> 01:17:24,392
What are they gonna do
with the bird?

978
01:17:24,475 --> 01:17:27,600
They're waiting to extract
the DNA with the Omnis,

979
01:17:27,683 --> 01:17:28,808
duplicate it,

980
01:17:28,891 --> 01:17:31,434
and then inject
all other animals

981
01:17:31,517 --> 01:17:35,683
so that knowledge
can spread and multiply.

982
01:17:35,766 --> 01:17:37,392
And cover the world.

983
01:17:37,475 --> 01:17:39,309
You'd better hurry.

984
01:17:45,975 --> 01:17:47,309
( gasps )

985
01:17:47,392 --> 01:17:49,891
( panting )

986
01:18:10,058 --> 01:18:13,225
( alarm wailing )

987
01:18:41,058 --> 01:18:42,975
- ( beeps )
- ( lock clicks )

988
01:18:47,183 --> 01:18:48,641
( beeps )

989
01:18:54,475 --> 01:18:56,766
( beeping )

990
01:19:04,267 --> 01:19:06,475
Beatty:
Master Trooper.

991
01:19:12,142 --> 01:19:14,142
I wasn't expecting
to see you.

992
01:19:14,225 --> 01:19:16,808
- Are you over your sickness?
- Yeah.

993
01:19:16,891 --> 01:19:18,559
You were right.
I just needed to rest.

994
01:19:18,641 --> 01:19:21,058
- I'm feelin' 100 now.
- Beautiful.

995
01:19:21,142 --> 01:19:23,309
- So you're with us.
- Yes, sir.

996
01:19:23,392 --> 01:19:25,725
We need to find the Omnis.
Any leads?

997
01:19:25,808 --> 01:19:31,100
Yuxie, have Fireman Douglas
and his squad report.

998
01:19:31,183 --> 01:19:33,267
Raid time.
I'm ready to gear up.

999
01:19:38,100 --> 01:19:40,434
What does two times two equal?

1000
01:19:41,559 --> 01:19:42,975
Excuse me?

1001
01:19:44,683 --> 01:19:46,350
Four.

1002
01:19:46,434 --> 01:19:48,475
Why? What's wrong?

1003
01:19:51,766 --> 01:19:53,891
Is that all
you have to say to me?

1004
01:19:53,975 --> 01:19:56,142
Of course.

1005
01:19:56,225 --> 01:19:58,933
John, just talk to me.
What's goin' on?

1006
01:19:59,017 --> 01:20:02,350
I, too, burn with desire.

1007
01:20:04,017 --> 01:20:08,683
But I would rather walk with
my brother in the darkness

1008
01:20:08,766 --> 01:20:10,975
than go alone in the light.

1009
01:20:11,058 --> 01:20:14,017
- Sir.
- Whatever happens tonight, Guy,

1010
01:20:14,100 --> 01:20:18,225
you should know I would
rather walk with my brother.

1011
01:20:19,850 --> 01:20:21,850
( footsteps approach )

1012
01:20:23,683 --> 01:20:25,641
Douglas,
report, please.

1013
01:20:26,683 --> 01:20:28,267
Found this
in the locker room, sir.

1014
01:20:28,350 --> 01:20:29,975
Beatty: Whose locker
did you find it in?

1015
01:20:30,058 --> 01:20:31,766
Nobody's. It was
just on the floor.

1016
01:20:31,850 --> 01:20:33,725
Like a dead rat.

1017
01:20:33,808 --> 01:20:35,225
Take it!

1018
01:20:35,309 --> 01:20:37,017
That's an order.

1019
01:20:38,725 --> 01:20:42,100
Go on. Read us
a bedtime story.

1020
01:20:42,183 --> 01:20:43,701
- ( lighter clicks )
- Let's burn this shit.

1021
01:20:43,725 --> 01:20:44,808
No, no, no, no, no, no.

1022
01:20:44,891 --> 01:20:47,475
A special tip came
directly to me tonight.

1023
01:20:47,559 --> 01:20:50,142
Might be a good lead
on the Omnis.

1024
01:20:50,225 --> 01:20:53,225
But let's finish
this little business first.

1025
01:20:53,309 --> 01:20:55,058
Open the book.

1026
01:20:56,350 --> 01:20:59,142
Oh, my.
Your pulse is really racing.

1027
01:20:59,225 --> 01:21:02,475
Steady now, Montag.
I wouldn't want to burn your hand off.

1028
01:21:02,559 --> 01:21:05,559
Now read.
Read to me.

1029
01:21:07,517 --> 01:21:11,475
"To go wrong
in one's own way

1030
01:21:11,559 --> 01:21:14,891
is better than to go right
in someone else's.

1031
01:21:16,725 --> 01:21:21,350
Taking a new step,
uttering a new word...

1032
01:21:21,434 --> 01:21:22,725
( snaps lighter shut )

1033
01:21:24,392 --> 01:21:27,058
...is what people
fear the most."

1034
01:21:27,142 --> 01:21:29,517
All those silly words,

1035
01:21:29,600 --> 01:21:33,517
those false promises,
the timeworn philosophies.

1036
01:21:33,600 --> 01:21:38,183
It's like chain-smoking,
chapter by chapter.

1037
01:21:38,267 --> 01:21:41,808
- Go on. Don't stop reading to me.
- Sir.

1038
01:21:41,891 --> 01:21:43,600
Next page!

1039
01:21:47,641 --> 01:21:49,850
"Did you think
that one tiny crime...

1040
01:21:49,933 --> 01:21:51,725
( lighter clicks )

1041
01:21:51,808 --> 01:21:55,891
...would be wiped out
by thousands of good deeds?

1042
01:21:55,975 --> 01:21:58,766
That there would be
no punishment?"

1043
01:22:04,891 --> 01:22:06,975
A little knowledge
is a dangerous thing.

1044
01:22:07,058 --> 01:22:09,808
You read a few lines, and you're
ready to blow up the world,

1045
01:22:09,891 --> 01:22:12,434
chop heads off,
destroy authority.

1046
01:22:12,517 --> 01:22:16,100
I know.
I've been through it all.

1047
01:22:18,142 --> 01:22:20,933
Now, what do you want to do?

1048
01:22:26,017 --> 01:22:28,058
I want to burn.

1049
01:22:28,142 --> 01:22:29,475
Hmm.

1050
01:22:30,683 --> 01:22:33,350
Montag.

1051
01:22:33,434 --> 01:22:34,559
My brother.

1052
01:22:34,641 --> 01:22:36,183
Let's burn.

1053
01:23:09,766 --> 01:23:11,559
Raven:
Good evening, Cleveland.

1054
01:23:11,641 --> 01:23:13,683
Live outside
Master Trooper Montag's home

1055
01:23:13,766 --> 01:23:15,891
where shocking events
are unfolding.

1056
01:23:17,683 --> 01:23:20,683
Montag! Do you have anything
to say to your fans?

1057
01:23:22,309 --> 01:23:23,350
Montag.

1058
01:23:23,434 --> 01:23:26,183
Something the matter,
Montag?

1059
01:23:30,142 --> 01:23:33,350
You wanted to fly
near the sun.

1060
01:23:33,434 --> 01:23:36,183
You burn your damn wings off
and you wonder why.

1061
01:23:38,058 --> 01:23:41,725
Go in. I'll give you a minute
to get your house in order.

1062
01:23:43,475 --> 01:23:44,933
Go on.

1063
01:23:51,559 --> 01:23:54,725
No one is lookin' out
for you now, boy.

1064
01:24:14,017 --> 01:24:19,142
Yuxie: Hello, Montag.
This is rather unfortunate.

1065
01:24:19,225 --> 01:24:21,267
Some people would like
to see you.

1066
01:24:28,933 --> 01:24:32,017
That's quite a collection
of graffiti you have there.

1067
01:24:32,100 --> 01:24:34,808
Your fans deserve
an explanation.

1068
01:24:34,891 --> 01:24:37,600
These aren't mine.
You set me up!

1069
01:24:39,142 --> 01:24:41,475
( footsteps approach )

1070
01:24:41,559 --> 01:24:44,517
Welcome, John.
I've been waiting for you.

1071
01:24:44,600 --> 01:24:46,225
Yuxie, go dark.

1072
01:24:49,267 --> 01:24:53,350
I told you I would burn you
if you betrayed me.

1073
01:24:53,434 --> 01:24:55,891
And this...

1074
01:24:55,975 --> 01:24:58,309
this is the big dance.

1075
01:25:00,517 --> 01:25:02,100
Douglas. Stone.

1076
01:25:02,183 --> 01:25:05,933
Yuxie! Let the fire show begin.

1077
01:25:07,309 --> 01:25:11,392
Now, you do what
you are trained to do.

1078
01:25:11,475 --> 01:25:13,725
All you know how to do.

1079
01:25:13,808 --> 01:25:15,309
Burn.

1080
01:26:01,142 --> 01:26:03,183
( panting )

1081
01:26:04,891 --> 01:26:07,725
You're not finished.
Go on.

1082
01:26:28,309 --> 01:26:30,017
( panting )

1083
01:26:32,559 --> 01:26:34,725
Free yourself.

1084
01:27:05,933 --> 01:27:08,183
Let's light him up.

1085
01:27:08,267 --> 01:27:11,183
Tell your fans
what time it is.

1086
01:27:11,267 --> 01:27:13,517
All: It's time to burn
for America again!

1087
01:27:13,600 --> 01:27:15,517
Say it, Montag.

1088
01:27:15,600 --> 01:27:17,183
- ( crowd jeering )
- Say it!

1089
01:27:17,267 --> 01:27:18,933
Woman:
Spit it out! Come on!

1090
01:27:23,933 --> 01:27:25,225
Come on, Captain.

1091
01:27:29,766 --> 01:27:31,559
Why did you do this?

1092
01:27:31,641 --> 01:27:35,475
- What did you find? Chaos.
- ( clamp clicks )

1093
01:27:35,559 --> 01:27:37,475
( device humming )

1094
01:27:42,933 --> 01:27:45,766
The Salamander
eats its own tail.

1095
01:27:48,309 --> 01:27:50,933
Master Trooper Douglas.

1096
01:27:51,017 --> 01:27:52,891
Master Trooper Douglas
reporting, sir.

1097
01:27:52,975 --> 01:27:55,891
- Tell us what you saw.
- Montag getting into a car

1098
01:27:55,975 --> 01:27:58,392
with Clarisse McClellan
and two known Eels.

1099
01:27:58,475 --> 01:28:00,641
Beatty: No wonder you've been
so eloquent lately.

1100
01:28:00,725 --> 01:28:03,683
But you're still
the same dog I raised,

1101
01:28:03,766 --> 01:28:07,600
just barking
at someone else's command.

1102
01:28:07,683 --> 01:28:10,267
Gather a squad,
find Clarisse and the other Eels

1103
01:28:10,350 --> 01:28:12,142
- and bring them to me.
- Yes, sir.

1104
01:28:14,517 --> 01:28:18,850
- Montag! Stop! Let it go! Drop it!
- Montag: Drop it, Douglas!

1105
01:28:18,933 --> 01:28:21,600
Well, that's one way
to win your fans back.

1106
01:28:21,683 --> 01:28:23,766
Beatty: Hold fire
till your brother speaks.

1107
01:28:23,850 --> 01:28:25,808
- Drop it, Douglas.
- Beatty: Go ahead,

1108
01:28:25,891 --> 01:28:27,371
pull the trigger,
let Douglas have it.

1109
01:28:27,434 --> 01:28:29,017
- Captain.
- Quiet, Douglas!

1110
01:28:29,100 --> 01:28:31,641
Could it be existence
is our exile

1111
01:28:31,725 --> 01:28:33,559
and nothingness is our home?

1112
01:28:33,641 --> 01:28:35,100
Fire is your home, Montag.

1113
01:28:35,183 --> 01:28:37,309
- Burn away.
- No, Captain, please!

1114
01:28:37,392 --> 01:28:40,183
What is called
a reason for living is also

1115
01:28:40,267 --> 01:28:42,850
an excellent reason
for dying.

1116
01:28:49,600 --> 01:28:53,350
( screaming )

1117
01:28:55,975 --> 01:29:00,600
( Douglas continues screaming )

1118
01:29:12,559 --> 01:29:15,517
Montag, you did it.

1119
01:29:16,891 --> 01:29:18,392
You did it.

1120
01:29:31,058 --> 01:29:33,559
( panting )

1121
01:29:33,641 --> 01:29:35,392
Choice.

1122
01:29:42,183 --> 01:29:45,559
( onlookers scream )

1123
01:29:50,725 --> 01:29:52,350
Beatty:
Dear Natives.

1124
01:29:52,434 --> 01:29:53,766
Eel Montag,

1125
01:29:53,850 --> 01:29:55,350
murderer Montag,

1126
01:29:55,434 --> 01:29:56,725
terrorist Montag,

1127
01:29:56,808 --> 01:30:00,517
has committed treason
against our nation.

1128
01:30:00,600 --> 01:30:03,142
Eyes on Axis-Cam,
eyes on the 9,

1129
01:30:03,225 --> 01:30:04,891
and report where
this terrorist is.

1130
01:30:04,975 --> 01:30:08,183
Terrorist Montag...
could he have the Omnis?

1131
01:30:08,267 --> 01:30:10,267
Stay vivid to find out.

1132
01:30:30,392 --> 01:30:33,517
- Montag: Where's Gustavo?
- Clarisse: They arrested him.

1133
01:30:33,600 --> 01:30:35,641
Transponder?

1134
01:30:35,725 --> 01:30:37,808
( beeps )

1135
01:30:40,975 --> 01:30:44,142
- Page 93.
- 93.

1136
01:30:49,267 --> 01:30:52,850
"I bequeath myself
to the dirt

1137
01:30:52,933 --> 01:30:55,434
to grow from
the grass I love.

1138
01:30:55,517 --> 01:30:59,766
If you want me again,
look for me under your boot soles.

1139
01:30:59,850 --> 01:31:03,891
You will hardly know who I am
or what I mean,

1140
01:31:03,975 --> 01:31:06,933
but I shall be good help
to you nevertheless,

1141
01:31:07,017 --> 01:31:10,434
and filter and fiber
your blood.

1142
01:31:10,517 --> 01:31:14,434
Failing to fetch me at first,
keep encouraged.

1143
01:31:14,517 --> 01:31:18,183
Missing me one place,
search another.

1144
01:31:18,267 --> 01:31:22,267
I stop somewhere,
waiting for you."

1145
01:31:22,350 --> 01:31:25,058
Yuxie: Found him.
He's heading to this black hole

1146
01:31:25,142 --> 01:31:26,434
outside Talay City.

1147
01:31:26,517 --> 01:31:29,350
Rerouting for
fastest arrival.

1148
01:31:30,975 --> 01:31:32,517
( engine revving )

1149
01:31:42,392 --> 01:31:45,683
- ( vehicles approach )
- Clifford, run!

1150
01:31:45,766 --> 01:31:48,350
- ( panicked shouting )
- Clifford!

1151
01:31:54,058 --> 01:31:55,183
( air brakes hiss )

1152
01:31:57,933 --> 01:32:00,058
( all shouting )

1153
01:32:27,933 --> 01:32:29,309
( Firemen shouting at Eels )

1154
01:32:33,350 --> 01:32:35,475
Male Eel: Get out of here!
Run! Run!

1155
01:32:35,559 --> 01:32:36,891
- Toni!
- Fireman: Don't you move!

1156
01:32:36,975 --> 01:32:40,392
- Get down!
- Get off of her!

1157
01:32:48,309 --> 01:32:52,559
Come on. Get up,
we gotta go.

1158
01:32:52,641 --> 01:32:53,933
Come on.

1159
01:33:15,808 --> 01:33:18,475
- ( flames whoosh )
- Fireman: Stand still!

1160
01:33:22,517 --> 01:33:26,434
Fireman: When I ask you not to move,
that means don't move!

1161
01:33:46,600 --> 01:33:48,808
( fire whooshing )

1162
01:33:52,517 --> 01:33:54,267
Hey. Clifford.

1163
01:33:54,350 --> 01:33:55,683
Hey. Come on.

1164
01:33:58,350 --> 01:33:59,683
( bird chirps )

1165
01:34:07,850 --> 01:34:09,683
( transponder beeps )

1166
01:34:21,641 --> 01:34:25,017
( chirping)

1167
01:34:28,850 --> 01:34:30,559
( chirping )

1168
01:34:47,100 --> 01:34:49,225
Omnis?

1169
01:34:54,350 --> 01:34:55,725
Stop.

1170
01:34:57,891 --> 01:35:00,475
I command you, Montag.

1171
01:35:00,559 --> 01:35:02,559
Stop.

1172
01:35:06,683 --> 01:35:08,725
( chirping )

1173
01:35:25,350 --> 01:35:29,975
( wings flapping )

1174
01:36:09,142 --> 01:36:11,975
( music playing,
no audible scream )

1175
01:36:32,434 --> 01:36:34,475
( wings flapping )

1176
01:37:09,350 --> 01:37:12,350
( music playing )

1177
01:37:46,058 --> 01:37:48,434
( music playing )
